title: feat(ngAnimate): add between callbacks
body:
We're currently working on the migration of AngularStrap/AngularUI-bootstrap to Bootstrap 3.0 + AngularJS 1.2.0.

We need theses callbacks to be able to properly handle element positioning (ie. tooltips, popovers) while still relying on the `$animate.enter`/`$animate.leave` syntax to leverage CSS animations.

Not sure unit testing is required for such a basic patch, will gladly add them if you want.

cc @matsko

feat($controllerProvider): Controller code resolution through DI.
body:
Allows array-notated constructors to use a controller name for their constructor
function, which permits reuse of controller code with different injectables.
Previously, we had to declare a function in the global context to actually reuse
functions with different injectables.  Now we can declare a controller
constructor inline and refer to it in other controller declarations through the
array notation.

fix(core): parse IE11 UA string correctly
body:
Ref:  http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/ms537503.aspx

It's great that IE11 wants to be compatible enough that it doesn't want
to be special cased and treated differently.

However, as long as one has to have a different code path for IE than
for the other supported browsers, we still need to detect and special
case it.  For instance, our URL parsing code still needs the same
workaround the we used for IE10.  We still see the same Access denied /
TypeError exceptions when setting certain values.  FYI, Angular doesn't
generally blindly test for IE  we also check the version number.

Thanks to modern.ie for the free IE11 test VM.

Closes #3682
